\

\Amfphp_Core_Amf_Types_Vector

A wrapper class that tells the serializer that we want a vector at the flash end. You should only populate the data array with instances of the same class. If you want to send back objects of different types, use the array class and not Vector.<*>, as Vector.<*> is not and will not be supported.

$fixed

$fixed :

Is the vector fixed length? VECTOR_VARIABLE_LENGTH for not-fixed length, VECTOR_FIXED_LENGTH for fixed. The default is VECTOR_VARIABLE_LENGTH.

Type

Tags

None found

$type

$type :

The type of vector. VECTOR_INT for int, VECTOR_UINT for uint, VECTOR_DOUBLE for float, and VECTOR_OBJECT for object. The default is object.

Type

Tags

None found

$className

$className :

The class of the vector if the vector is an object vector. You should set this and not $_explicitType on individual objects now. The latter will be phased out.
